    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/rh-index-comparison-5pt",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index comparison at 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values were compared against in-vitro experimental measurements from the FDA generic centrifugal pump loop at five flow-speed combinations (Q = 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 L/min; N = 2000, 2500, 3000, 3500, 4000 RPM). The Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model was applied to Lagrangian particle tracks seeded uniformly at the pump inlet. RH predictions fell within ±15% of experimental values at 4 of 5 operating points; the outlier at maximum speed showed 22% over-prediction consistent with known turbulence-model limitations near the volute tongue. The experimental campaign was conducted at the FDA CDRH flow-loop facility using bovine blood with haematocrit 33 ± 2%, following ASTM F1841 preparation protocol. Uncertainty in experimental RH was ±8% (k=2). The simulation campaign used ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 on a 14.2 M polyhedral mesh with SST k-ω turbulence closure; mesh independence was confirmed at the 3 L/min, 3000 RPM reference point prior to the full sweep. This validation result is the primary evidence supporting the hemolysis QoI claim and carries the highest evidentiary weight in the credibility argument.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-generic-pump-experimental-rh-dataset"
